{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "edtech-auth-collection",
		"name": "EdTech - API Authentification",
		"description": "Collection Postman pour tester l'API d'authentification du système EdTech.\n\n**Base URL:** http://localhost:3000\n\n**Endpoints disponibles:**\n- Inscription (Register)\n- Connexion (Login)\n- Health Check",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
	"item": [
		{
			"name": "Authentication",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Register - Admin",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
									"    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.environment.set(\"auth_token\", jsonData.token);",
									"    pm.environment.set(\"user_id\", jsonData.user.id);",
									"    console.log(\"Token saved:\", jsonData.token);",
									"}",
									"",
									"pm.test(\"Status code is 201\", function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test(\"Response has token\", function () {",
									"    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('token');",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test(\"Response has user object\", function () {",
									"    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('user');",
									"    pm.expect(jsonData.user).to.have.property('email');",
									"    pm.expect(jsonData.user).to.have.property('role');",
									"});"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"admin@edtech.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Admin123!\",\n  \"role\": \"ADMIN\"\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/register",
							"host": [
								"{{base_url}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"api",
								"auth",
								"register"
							]
						},
						"description": "Créer un nouveau compte administrateur.\n\n**Rôles disponibles:**\n- `ADMIN` - Administrateur\n- `TEACHER` - Enseignant\n\n**Body (JSON):**\n```json\n{\n  \"email\": \"admin@edtech.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Admin123!\",\n  \"role\": \"ADMIN\"\n}\n```\n\n**Réponse (201):**\n```json\n{\n  \"token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIs...\",\n  \"user\": {\n    \"id\": 1,\n    \"email\": \"admin@edtech.com\",\n    \"role\": \"ADMIN\"\n  }\n}\n```"
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Register - Teacher",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
									"    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
									"    console.log(\"Teacher registered successfully\");",
									"}",
									"",
									"pm.test(\"Status code is 201\", function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test(\"User role is TEACHER\", function () {",
									"    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.expect(jsonData.user.role).to.eql('TEACHER');",
									"});"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"teacher@edtech.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Teacher123!\",\n  \"role\": \"TEACHER\"\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/register",
							"host": [
								"{{base_url}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"api",
								"auth",
								"register"
							]
						},
						"description": "Créer un nouveau compte enseignant."
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Login",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
									"    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.environment.set(\"auth_token\", jsonData.token);",
									"    pm.environment.set(\"user_id\", jsonData.user.id);",
									"    pm.environment.set(\"user_email\", jsonData.user.email);",
									"    pm.environment.set(\"user_role\", jsonData.user.role);",
									"    console.log(\"Logged in as:\", jsonData.user.email);",
									"}",
									"",
									"pm.test(\"Status code is 200\", function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test(\"Response has token\", function () {",
									"    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('token');",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test(\"Token is saved in environment\", function () {",
									"    pm.expect(pm.environment.get(\"auth_token\")).to.not.be.undefined;",
									"});"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"admin@edtech.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Admin123!\"\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/login",
							"host": [
								"{{base_url}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"api",
								"auth",
								"login"
							]
						},
						"description": "Se connecter avec un compte existant.\n\n**Body (JSON):**\n```json\n{\n  \"email\": \"admin@edtech.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Admin123!\"\n}\n```\n\n**Réponse (200):**\n```json\n{\n  \"token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIs...\",\n  \"user\": {\n    \"id\": 1,\n    \"email\": \"admin@edtech.com\",\n    \"role\": \"ADMIN\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Erreurs possibles:**\n- `400` - Email ou mot de passe manquant\n- `401` - Email ou mot de passe incorrect"
					},
					"response": []
				}
			],
			"description": "Endpoints d'authentification (inscription et connexion)"
		},
		{
			"name": "Health Check",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Server Health",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"pm.test(\"Status code is 200\", function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test(\"Server status is ok\", function () {",
									"    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.expect(jsonData.status).to.eql('ok');",
									"});"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/health",
							"host": [
								"{{base_url}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"api",
								"health"
							]
						},
						"description": "Vérifier que le serveur fonctionne correctement.\n\n**Réponse (200):**\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"ok\",\n  \"message\": \"Server is running\"\n}\n```"
					},
					"response": []
				}
			],
			"description": "Endpoint de vérification de l'état du serveur"
		},
		{
			"name": "Protected Routes (Examples)",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Example - Get User Profile",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"pm.test(\"Status code is 200 or 401\", function () {",
									"    pm.expect([200, 401]).to.include(pm.response.code);",
									"});",
									"",
									"if (pm.response.code === 401) {",
									"    console.log(\"Not authenticated - please login first\");",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"auth": {
							"type": "bearer",
							"bearer": [
								{
									"key": "token",
									"value": "{{auth_token}}",
									"type": "string"
								}
							]
						},
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/user/profile",
							"host": [
								"{{base_url}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"api",
								"user",
								"profile"
							]
						},
						"description": "**Exemple de route protégée**\n\nCette route nécessite un token JWT valide.\n\nLe token est automatiquement ajouté depuis la variable d'environnement `auth_token` après un login réussi.\n\n**Headers requis:**\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer <token>\n```"
					},
					"response": []
				}
			],
			"description": "Exemples de routes nécessitant une authentification JWT"
		}
